# Listen Importer

Use this skill when a user wants to bring local audio or transcripts into Listen. The importer scans local sources, caches files locally, optionally preprocesses/downsamples audio, optionally transcribes audio, and uploads/publishes Listen conversations.

## Success Criteria

- Local source data is scanned into `~/.listen-importer`.
- Audio is preprocessed/downsampled when useful for transcription or upload size.
- Audio without transcripts is transcribed with the chosen provider.
- Imported conversations are uploaded with `--publish` so they appear in Listen.
- Imported source labels match Listen: `recorder`, `voice_memos`, `voxterm`, or `soundcore_sync`.

## Prerequisites

- Bun installed.
- TinyCloud CLI `tc` installed and authenticated for the user's Listen space.
- For transcription: `ASSEMBLYAI_API_KEY` or `DEEPGRAM_API_KEY`.
- For Apple Voice Memos: macOS and Full Disk Access for the terminal app may be required.
- For recorder imports: the recorder volume must be mounted, for example `/Volumes/MIC MINI`.

## Pull In The Importer

Use the GitHub-backed npx command for one-off runs:

```sh
npx --yes github:TinyCloudLabs/listen-importer init
npx --yes github:TinyCloudLabs/listen-importer doctor
```

For active development or repeated local work:

```sh
git clone https://github.com/TinyCloudLabs/listen-importer.git
cd listen-importer
bun install
bun link
listen-importer init
listen-importer doctor
```

If `npx` cannot run the Bun shebang in the user's environment, use the clone/link workflow.

## Storage Contract

Local state defaults to:

```text
~/.listen-importer/
  listen-importer.sqlite
  media/
  downsampled/
  transcripts/
```

Remote Listen storage defaults to:

```text
SQL database: xyz.tinycloud.listen/conversations
KV prefix:    xyz.tinycloud.listen
```

Use `LISTEN_IMPORTER_HOME=/path/to/state` to isolate a run. Use `--profile` or `--host` on upload/auth commands when the TinyCloud CLI profile or host must be explicit.

## Agent Workflow

1. Ask what source to import: recorder volume, Apple Voice Memos, VoxTerm transcripts, Soundcore Sync transcripts, or all known local sources.
2. Ask for path/time window when needed: recorder mount path, VoxTerm/Soundcore transcript directory, and Voice Memos `--since`.
3. Run `doctor`, then a dry run if the command supports it.
4. Scan source data.
5. Run `status --json` and inspect counts.
6. Preprocess/downsample audio before transcription or size-sensitive upload.
7. Transcribe missing transcripts with AssemblyAI or Deepgram.
8. Upload with `--publish`, usually with `--use-downsampled` after preprocessing.
9. Run `status --json` again and report imported/published counts plus any failures.

Do not import deleted Voice Memos unless the user explicitly asks for `--include-deleted`.

## Source Commands

Recorder volume:

```sh
listen-importer scan /Volumes/MIC\ MINI --recorder mic-mini
listen-importer scan /path/to/recorder --recorder generic
```

Apple Voice Memos:

```sh
listen-importer scan-source voice-memos
listen-importer scan-source voice-memos --since yesterday
listen-importer scan-source voice-memos --since 2026-05-25
listen-importer scan-source voice-memos --include-deleted
```

VoxTerm markdown transcripts:

```sh
listen-importer scan-source voxterm
listen-importer scan-source voxterm --path ~/Documents/voxterm-transcripts
```

Soundcore Sync markdown transcripts:

```sh
listen-importer scan-source soundcore-sync
listen-importer scan-source soundcore-sync --path ~/Documents/Soundcore-Transcripts
```

If `--since` is omitted for app-library sources, the importer defaults to local midnight seven calendar days ago.

## Preprocess And Transcribe

Downsampling is non-destructive. Originals stay in `media/`; derived files go to `downsampled/`.

```sh
listen-importer preprocess --source all
listen-importer preprocess --source voice_memos --format mp3 --bitrate 64k --sample-rate 16000
listen-importer status --source all --json
```

Transcription prefers downsampled audio when available:

```sh
ASSEMBLYAI_API_KEY=... listen-importer transcribe --source all --provider assemblyai
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=... listen-importer transcribe --source all --provider deepgram
```

Use `--api-key` only when the user wants to pass a key directly. Prefer environment variables so secrets do not get copied into shell history.

## Upload And Publish

Publish makes rows visible in Listen:

```sh
listen-importer upload --publish --use-downsampled --source all
listen-importer upload --publish --transcripts-only --source voxterm
listen-importer upload --publish --transcripts-only --source soundcore_sync
```

Use source-specific upload commands when keeping workflows separated:

```sh
listen-importer upload --publish --use-downsampled --source recorder
listen-importer upload --publish --use-downsampled --source voice_memos
listen-importer upload --publish --transcripts-only --source voxterm
listen-importer upload --publish --transcripts-only --source soundcore_sync
```

## Useful Commands

```text
listen-importer init
listen-importer auth [--profile name] [--host url]
listen-importer permissions [--to did] [--expiry 30d]
listen-importer scan <path> [--recorder mic-mini|generic] [--dry-run]
listen-importer scan-source voice-memos|voxterm|soundcore-sync [--since yesterday|YYYY-MM-DD] [--path path] [--include-deleted] [--dry-run]
listen-importer status [--source recorder|voice_memos|voxterm|soundcore_sync|all] [--json]
listen-importer list [--limit n] [--source recorder|voice_memos|voxterm|soundcore_sync|all]
listen-importer preprocess [--limit n] [--source recorder|voice_memos|voxterm|soundcore_sync|all] [--format mp3|m4a|wav] [--bitrate 64k] [--sample-rate 16000] [--force]
listen-importer downsample [--limit n] [--source recorder|voice_memos|voxterm|soundcore_sync|all] [--format mp3|m4a|wav] [--bitrate 64k] [--sample-rate 16000] [--force]
listen-importer transcribe [--limit n] [--source recorder|voice_memos|voxterm|soundcore_sync|all] [--provider deepgram|assemblyai] [--api-key key] [--force]
listen-importer upload [--limit n] [--publish] [--use-downsampled] [--transcripts-only] [--source recorder|voice_memos|voxterm|soundcore_sync|all] [--profile name] [--host url]
listen-importer doctor
```

## Final Report Format

Report:

- source imported
- scan counts
- downsample/preprocess counts
- transcription counts and provider
- upload/publish counts
- local state path
- any failed recordings and next command to retry
